prompt:
Add a public class called Product to Domain.calr with a public property called Price of type i32.

Use this exact Calor property syntax:
§CL{c001:Product:pub}
  §PROP{Price:i32:pub}
§/CL{c001}

The §PROP{name:type:visibility} syntax defines an auto-property:
- name is the property name
- type is the property type
- visibility is pub/priv/prot
- Auto-properties have default getter and setter
